  "elapsed_s": 10.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, prior to that time, we were a, I would call it a low-middle class family.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my father's business was [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] from-- changed when he lost his store.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And at that time, he was in business of selling felt, which is for making hats and the accessories of the hat making, accessories like the leather inside of the hat, and so on.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he had no license, so it was a risky business.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because his previous connection with some of the industrial people and his persuasion that they would let him have the merchandise even without his license has been that he, he kind of illegally was selling those without the proper license.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we were always very fearful that if he caught, what would happen.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And as the anti-Jewish laws progressed further, so did the, so did the business decline.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because even those factories were very unwilling.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he, at the end, only had one place which was willing to supply him without his license.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, father and mother both loved reading, and newspapers as well as, as other literature.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And father bought the daily newspaper in Hungary, a paper which was called the I remember that very well and the whole logo and how it looked like.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that paper appeared in our home daily.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so did the Jewish weekly.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the Jewish weekly was also an important part of the reading.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I have seen that paper regularly.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I have started early.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was taken to kindergarten and, and after that, to elementary school at age six.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And from age six till 10, I attended an elementary school.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was in a neighborhood of the 14th district of Budapest on a street called [HUNGARIAN], which means-- Ut means avenue.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
